		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Laia Abril &#8211; Photojournalist]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://www.scrollstudios.com/en/projects/laia-abril/" />
		<id>http://www.scrollstudios.com/?p=295</id>
		<updated>2010-10-13T16:40:08Z</updated>
		<published>2010-09-15T11:59:53Z</published>
		<category scheme="http://www.scrollstudios.com" term="CMS" /><category scheme="http://www.scrollstudios.com" term="web development" /><category scheme="http://www.scrollstudios.com" term="Interface design" /><category scheme="http://www.scrollstudios.com" term="web design" /><category scheme="http://www.scrollstudios.com" term="projects-entries" /><category scheme="http://www.scrollstudios.com" term="wireframing" />		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[With the elasticity in mind, we did a site where the content is shown in a different way depending on the screen resolution and the device of the user.]]></summary>
		<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.scrollstudios.com/en/projects/laia-abril/"><![CDATA[<p><p>Laia Abril is a photojournalist from Barcelona based in Treviso (Italy). Apart from being chief editor of Colors Magazine in Fabrica (Benetton), Laia is travelling around the world doing photojournalism. The photographer wanted a site where she could show her work with impact in a clear way. She was very interested also in having website that adapts to the different visitor&#8217;s resources, an <strong>elastic site</strong>.</p>
<p>Working with the elasticity on mind, this website is showing the content in a different way <strong>depending on the screen resolution and the device</strong> of the user. We worked in what it is called a responsive design and development. Because this site is very visual based, we enriched the intereaction for tactile devices ( iPad, iPhone,etc.) so you can browse between the pictures of a photo gallery using swipe gestures.</p></p>
]]></content>
